records.addlTxt:
Defendant Marques Jeovon Henry in court with attorney Hazel Jean Washington.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 2:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant sentenced to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence with credit for 3 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Defendant sentenced to serve 1 MONTH in the House of Correction.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS.

Conditions as to both counts:
*  Comply with all conditions of probation;
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety; to be monitored by random urine screens;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
